<!--
  Android Lint baseline (issues #331, #334).

  Burned down from 44 entries to 34 in #334. Every entry that REMAINS is justified
  below; nothing here is a "we'll get to it". The baseline may only ever shrink — if a
  fix removes one, regenerate (delete this file, run `./gradlew :app:lintDebug`) and
  RE-ADD THIS HEADER, which regeneration discards.

  Per issue #334 AC#2, no @SuppressLint / tools:ignore annotations were added anywhere
  to dodge a fix. The 10 that went were real fixes:
  UseKtx x3 (SharedPreferences.edit {}), HardcodedText x3 (widget placeholders moved to
  string resources), ObsoleteSdkInt x1 (drawable-v21 merged into drawable — minSdk 29
  means the v21 qualifier could never lose), UnusedResources x1 (bg_widget_label was
  orphaned; wired it to the widget receiver, which is what it was written for), and
  StaticFieldLeak x1 (GarminSender now takes an Application rather than a bare Context,
  encoding in the type the invariant every call site was already honouring).

  REMAINING, and why:

  * LogNotTimber (24) — INAPPLICABLE. Lint sees com.jakewharton.timber on the classpath
    and suggests it over android.util.Log, but Timber is a TRANSITIVE dependency (it
    arrives via pumpx2), not one this app chose. Adopting a transitive library as the
    native logging framework would couple our logging to pumpx2's dependency graph and
    break on any upgrade that drops it. The native side uses android.util.Log
    deliberately; the Dart side has its own appLog. Revisit only if Timber ever becomes
    a direct, intentional dependency.

  * UnusedAttribute (5) — DELIBERATE FORWARD COMPATIBILITY. usesPermissionFlags (API
    31+), enableOnBackInvokedCallback (API 33+), previewLayout / targetCellWidth /
    targetCellHeight (API 31+). All are correct on the devices that read them and are
    ignored below; minSdk is 29. bg_widget_info.xml says as much in its own comment.
    Removing them would degrade behaviour on modern devices to silence a warning.

  * GradleDependency (3) — OWNED BY DEPENDABOT (decision-14). desugar_jdk_libs,
    androidx.core:core-ktx and androidx.test:core have newer releases. Version currency
    is Dependabot's job; bumping them by hand here would race its PRs and mix an
    unreviewed upgrade into an unrelated change. These entries are expected to churn as
    new versions ship — that is the mechanism working, not a debt.

  * TypographyDashes (1) — WRONG SUGGESTION HERE. Lint wants an em dash in the widget's
    "--" placeholder, but that string must byte-match what WidgetRenderModel writes at
    runtime for the no-reading case (WidgetRenderModel.kt: `cgmMgdl == null -> "--"`).
    Using an em dash would make the pre-data widget render differently from the live
    no-data state. Introduced by #334's own HardcodedText fix, and accepted knowingly:
    net effect of that fix is still -3 warnings.
-->
